results.name: Number of non-isomorphic intersecting set systems of weight n with empty intersection.
comment: A set system is a finite set of finite nonempty sets. It is intersecting if no two parts are disjoint. The weight of a set system is the sum of sizes of its parts. Weight is generally not the same as number of vertices.
